{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/8435", "repo": "rails", "body": "> I completely understand the need for class_eval, but is there a performance decrease by just using the instance variable method within a class eval?\r\n\r\nYes, if it replaces direct `@ivar` access. I also find\r\n```ruby\r\ndef foo\r\n  @foo\r\nend\r\n```\r\nto be more readable than:\r\n```ruby\r\ndef foo\r\n  instance_variable_get(:@foo)\r\nend\r\n```", "_id": {"$oid": "5237f33abd3543c15100a7b8"}, "issue_id": 8435, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/11124650", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/8435#issuecomment-11124650", "updated_at": "2012-12-07T09:59:16Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone", "login": "thedarkone", "gravatar_id": "c203190318ed9534390c93d1744a6cf1", "html_url": "https://github.com/thedarkone", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/c203190318ed9534390c93d1744a6cf1?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F68e4593563e1b425a7717504bca103d6.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 15688, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/thedarkone/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-12-07T09:59:16Z", "id": 11124650, "owner": "rails"}
